# SoroSense frontend — example env. Copy to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and fill in what you need.
#
# EVERY var here is NEXT_PUBLIC_*: Next inlines them into the browser bundle, so they are public by
# construction. Never put a secret in this file or in `.env.local`. The backend-only keys
# (`KEEPER_SECRET`, `FAUCET_ISSUER_SECRET`) live in the backend's env and never reach the client — the
# frontend only ever posts `{ address, currency }` to the faucet and gets a public tx hash back.
#
# All of these are OPTIONAL. With none of them set the app runs exactly as it does today: local
# fixtures, no network, no request. That is the offline default vitest and Playwright depend on.

# ── Backend read surface (STE-52b) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Origin of the backend's Hono API. UNSET ⇒ the frontend issues no request at all and falls back to its
# local derivations; there is deliberately NO default (a silent localhost default would make a
# production build hammer a host that isn't there).
#
# Boot the backend in mock mode (offline, deterministic stub FX) and point this at it:
#   pnpm -C backend exec tsx src/http/server.ts
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8787

# ── Wallet balance + faucet trustline (U4) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Horizon endpoint for reading the user's real stablecoin trustline balance. Unset ⇒ the fixture balance.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_HORIZON_URL=https://horizon-testnet.stellar.org

# Public issuer accounts of the self-issued testnet stablecoins. Needed to build the `changeTrust`
# operation the faucet's 409 asks for. Public keys — safe to ship to the browser.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_USDC_ISSUER=G...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_EURC_ISSUER=G...

# ── Test harness ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to "1" only by Playwright: swaps the wallet for the deterministic e2e stub (`lib/wallet.ts`).
# Never set this in a real run.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_E2E=1
